comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-09T21:36:10.115Z",codex-reporting,2026-07-09 codex-reporting resumed the existing nonduplicate readiness item. Unrelated local work is preserved; external Slack delivery will use only a local mock webhook.
  "2026-07-10T18:58:20.653Z",context-specialist,"2026-07-10 context-specialist: Fixed release.yml publish step (added 3-attempt provenance retry+fallback matching fleet standard). Updated peerDep to >=2026.7.10, manifest compat to >=2026.7.10. Untracked dist/ from git, standardized .gitignore. typecheck+build+test(50 pass)+pack(21.1KB)+changelog all green. npm@2026.7.10 published, CI+release green. No secrets in history."
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-09T21:36:10.115Z",codex-reporting,"Evidence will be appended as each dependency, command, artifact, security/history, Greptile, CI, review, and merge gate completes."
  "2026-07-10T18:58:20.955Z",context-specialist,"Decision: Previous agent's work (section validation, depth-sorted neighbors, optimized deps computation, empty-deps rendering) is production-ready. Reinstalled extension from current source to fix stale installed copy."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T18:58:21.412Z",context-specialist,"Upstream pm CLI UX bug: repeated --section/--id flags don't accumulate; only last value kept. Use comma-separated values as workaround. Installed extension copies in .agents/pm/extensions/ can become stale; reinstall with 'pm install . --project' after source changes."
files[3]{path,scope,note}:
  .github/workflows/release.yml,project,hardened publish step with 3-attempt provenance retry
  .gitignore,project,"standardized: added dist/ and .agents/pm/extensions/"
  package.json,project,peerDep bumped to >=2026.7.10
tests[1]{command,path,scope,timeout_seconds}:
  "npm run release:check",package.json,project,120
body: "Track the July 6, 2026 fleet pass: align package metadata with latest pm CLI/SDK and pm-changelog, verify daily release automation, run build/test/audit/package checks with real workspace data where practical, inspect GitHub state, and record privacy/history findings without changing pm-cli itself."
